I am an adorable, black short-haired male kitten.&nbsp; I am a sweetheart who will be the first to greet you and will squeak to get your attention.&nbsp; I am a lively, happy boy.&nbsp; 
I was found wandering alone near the Ventura Veterinarian Hospital.&nbsp; The staff introduced me to a litter of female kittens.&nbsp; I was so happy to find myself with three older sister.&nbsp; I&nbsp; will thrive in a home with one of my adopted sisters Garbo, Greta and Grisha.&nbsp; I am looking for that special someone who will cherish and love me, and will provide an indoor only home.&nbsp; Kids must be preteens or older -- no young kids.&nbsp;
Call 805-649-2844 or send email to greyfootcat@gmail.com
vaccinated &amp; dewormed --I will be spayed, felv/fiv tested &amp; microchipped on May 20.

Tanner came to us at 6 weeks old with major swelling in his face. It turned out to be several abscesses and he had to have 2 surgeries and drains put in as soon as he arrived with our rescue. He is one tough little pup because he recovered well and is now in his foster home awaiting his forever home. He is a sweet, happy, cuddly little boy and would love a home of his own! Great with kids and other dogs. Fill out the application today!

&nbsp;

Please consider sponsoring Tanner&nbsp;with either a one-time or monthly tax-deductible donation. Your donation will help It&#39;s The Pits with day-to-day care, including food, vaccinations, flea treatment, treats and toys. Click on the Sponsor This Pet link above to make your donation today. Thank you!

Sarge is an active long legged boy, who loves playing fetch, enjoys running around in his foster's large fenced in yard. He also enjoys jogging next to a bike &amp; would love to be someone's running partner. Despite being an active boy who will require an active owner, Sarge easily settles and really enjoys relaxing on the couch or bed taking cat naps.&nbsp;&nbsp; 
He is extremely affectionate, doesn't shed and he's very tolerant of his feet being washed with a wet cloth when coming indoors.&nbsp; Sarge grew up around children, but may knock over little ones due to his large size. &nbsp;He will likely do best in a home free of babies and toddlers. Sarge is potty trained and is crated 9.5 hours each work day. He uses and requires durable dog toys to keep him occupied during that time. He is not kenneled during the night, sleeps in the bedroom on his doggie bed. &nbsp;Sarge needs a little work on how to meet other dogs because he is so friendly some dogs are nervous. &nbsp;He is doing better but still needs coaching meeting new people outside of the home.&nbsp;&nbsp; Does well at home where he feels comfortable. 
Sarge's ideal home will have a securely fenced yard to keep him safely at home.&nbsp; Please&nbsp; fill out an&nbsp;ADOPTION or FOSTER APPLICATION&nbsp;by clicking on the FOSTER or ADOPT button below.   Thank You!

Jax is an 8-month old male Pit mix that we rescued from Santa Clara County.&nbsp;



Very gentle pup with a huge heart
Great with other dogs
Super sweetheart who loves to be with his people
Showing himself to be very obedient
Amazing on&nbsp;leash 90% of the time
As a young guy, has two speeds: energetic and super mellow&nbsp;
Would love to cuddle on the bed or couch (but currently isn&#39;t allowed to)&nbsp;



Adoption fee: $250, includes neuter and current vaccinations.&nbsp;Additional donations always welcome.&nbsp;



If you are interested in adopting this dog please visit this link&nbsp;to get the adoption process started.



We hold adoption events from San Francisco to the South Bay. Most dogs will be ready to go home the day of the adoption event. We accept credit cards and cash for our adoption fees. While adoption events are a great showcase for these amazing dogs, you don&#39;t need an adoption event to adopt a dog.&nbsp; Check out our adoptable pups, submit an application, and then meet them at their foster home!



We try to post the dogs that are attending on Facebook before the event, please visit and like us on Facebook.



To View other dogs up for adoption please visit our website.

TOM&nbsp;is such a sweet boy, so sad to be living on the streets of Phoenix in this heat! &nbsp;Now safely in Rescue, he will never have to worry about his next meal or a soft place to sleep. &nbsp;You are safe now, little man. &nbsp; TOM has some fabulous ears, he&#39;s ready to take off! &nbsp; TOM&nbsp;has been neutered, microchipped and vaccinated. &nbsp;Tom has lots of energy and loves to play! &nbsp;If you would like to meet him, please complete an application at www.helpadogsmile.org and his foster mom will contact you.

TOM&#39;s adoption fee will help with expenses of the Rescue.

