PANDORA is an adorable brown and tan tabby kitten with a white muzzle and eyeliner, and dark dramatic dark stripes on her back.&nbsp; She&#39;s about 10 weeks old.&nbsp; She was born to a stray momma cat who gave birth to her litter in one of our loving WCDC foster homes.&nbsp; Pandora is very friendly and is frequently the first to greet visitors.&nbsp; She is a naturally happy kitten who enjoys playing with toy mice that squeak, and feather-on-a-stick toys.&nbsp; She loves to climb, and can go up and down cat trees and scratching posts with ease.&nbsp; When she is finally worn out, she is a good snuggler.&nbsp; Pandora is an energetic young kitten who would do best in a household with another playful young cat, a friendly cat-savvy dog, or where someone is home most of the time to monitor her and give her lots of attention. &nbsp; 
Her adoption fee is $110, which is strictly to help cover our costs. She has been tested for FIV and feline leukemia (she is negative), spayed, microchipped, vaccinated, defleaed and dewormed&mdash;plus you get a free vet visit.&nbsp;&nbsp;


Pandora&nbsp;

is currently in the cat room at Petsmart in South Eugene (28th&nbsp;and Willamette), and can be seen there any time they are open.&nbsp; For more information, please call Beth at (541) 255-9296.

Hello! I&#39;m Cletus. I love to cuddle and get ear scratches but can be&nbsp;timid around new people.&nbsp;I am doing well on my house training and am currently puppy pad trained, but still have some work to do when it comes to walking on leash. I am 
&nbsp;not crate trained and we are working on this since I don&#39;t like to be crated&nbsp;at all. Small children make me nervous so a home with no kids or older kids would be best for me.

&nbsp;It will take me a few&nbsp;days to feel safe in a&nbsp;new home. I&nbsp;am kind of a&nbsp;nervous Nelly. I am your typical chihuahua. But once I am settled in and feel comfortable I am a little love bug.







