Sweetie Pie is&nbsp;He is a 15 year old neutered male.&nbsp; He has hyperthyroidism and needs daily meds.&nbsp; The meds are a gel that is rubbed into his ear and he is very good about it.&nbsp; My 93 year old mother was able to do this by herself.&nbsp; He was boarded from 2/9/16 until 4/29/16 when I thought I found him a new home.&nbsp; Yesterday I got an emergency call to come and get him so I had to take him back to be boarded again.&nbsp; He is a friendly and talkative &nbsp;indoor cat. His owner unfortunately passed away and is now trying to find a home to live out the rest of his days! 
Please contact Kathleen at&nbsp;817-929-9226 if you can help this guy live out his retirement years in a loving forever home!&nbsp;
courtesy post thru Trinity GAP Rescue!

This gorgeous baby appears to be between five &nbsp;and six months, and loves to be held! &nbsp;He came in with his sister, Joni, but sadly, is extremely scared and timid in the shelter. &nbsp;However, when you pick him up and hold him close, his personality just blossoms. &nbsp;He appears to be a King Charles Spaniel mix, and everyone took turns carrying him around like royalty. &nbsp;He is going to be a small dog who will make some lucky family/person a perfectly awesome dog. &nbsp;&nbsp;We need to get this baby (and sister Joni) out of the shelter ASAP because they are very sressed-out by all the shelter noises. &nbsp;If you can help, please contact the shelter today. &nbsp;
(chachi is in blue!)
***If you're interested in me, please contact the Euless Animal Shelter at 1517 Westpark Way in Euless - &nbsp;817-685-1594 and PLEASE REFER TO MY PET ID #. Thank you!***

Waffles' personality can be summed up in one word "vivacious"! &nbsp;This Schnauzer mix came in with BFF, Dibbles. &nbsp;Both were found wandering the streets in Arlington, but taken to the Euless Emergency vet which is how they &nbsp;got to the Euless Shelter. &nbsp;Since he was pretty matted, the vet kindly gave him a new groom, and he is so cute!!! &nbsp;He walks great on a leash, loves everybody, and gets along well with other dogs. &nbsp;He is young, around a year old, and already neutered. &nbsp;Waffles weighs in at 18.2 pounds, so is a perfect size for about anything from your lap to a great walking companion. &nbsp;He is just a great little dog!&nbsp;
&nbsp;
***If you're interested in me, please contact the Euless Animal Shelter at 1517 Westpark Way in Euless - &nbsp;817-685-1594 and PLEASE REFER TO MY PET ID #16483. Thank you!***

