Shadow comes to us from a local shelter. &nbsp;His owners were no longer able to care for him. &nbsp;We think he&#39;s less than 6 months old, and probably a German Shepherd Dog mix of some sort. &nbsp;He has huge paws, so we are expecting that he will be a big boy! &nbsp;He&#39;s silly, goofy, and loves to play with other dogs. &nbsp;We do not know how he is around cats, but he tested with them fine at the shelter. &nbsp;

If you&#39;re ready for an XL super-puppy boy to romp around in your home, Shadow might be the one! &nbsp;We have specific requirements around adopting a puppy. &nbsp;Please read &quot;Adoption Info.&quot;

Email inquiries can be made to PawsCrossedDogRescue@yahoo.com

Meet Nancy!!! &nbsp;This&nbsp;sweet senior gal&nbsp;is a Lab mix, approximately 8&nbsp;years old, and weighing about 80&nbsp;pounds. &nbsp; Nancy gets along with people and with other dogs. Her coat is actually has beautiful brown undertones. She is very loving and would make a perfect addition to any home. She is perfection, to say the least :)

Here&#39;s what Nancy&#39;s foster mom says about her:&nbsp; If you know of anyone looking for a big beautiful enthusiastic Lab mix girl who thinks she is a lap dog, who&#39;s well behaved, knows basic obedience, likes dogs and kids and lots and lots of love, Nancy is the dog for you!&nbsp; &nbsp;Her teeth are pearly white and she runs around like a young dog. &nbsp;no signs of being a senior other than her gray fur on her muzzle. 

If you are interested in meeting Nancy go to EHRDOGS.ORG and submit an application. &nbsp;Don&#39;t forget to ask for NANCY&nbsp;LONESTAR!!!! &nbsp;
